oadcast {type: fill, trade, profit}\n    AC-->>FE: Real-time update\n    FE->>FE: Update grid visualization + P&L\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Reconciliation — Safety Net\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant RW as ReconciliationWorker<br/>(every 15s)\n    participant EX as Bybit Exchange\n    participant DB as PostgreSQL\n    participant SQ as Sidekiq\n    participant FW as OrderFillWorker\n\n    Note over RW: Triggered every 15s OR on WebSocket disconnect\n\n    RW->>EX: GET /v5/order/realtime (all open orders, paginated)\n    RW->>DB: Load all DB orders with status=open\n\n    Note over RW: Compare exchange state vs DB state\n\n    alt Order in DB but NOT on exchange\n        RW->>EX: GET /v5/order/history (check if filled)\n        alt Was filled (missed by WebSocket)\n            RW->>SQ: Enqueue OrderFillWorker(order_data)\n            SQ->>FW: Process missed fill\n        else Was cancelled/rejected\n            RW->>DB: Mark order cancelled\n        end\n    end\n\n    alt Order on exchange but NOT in DB (orphan)\n        alt Matches bot's link_id pattern\n            RW->>DB: Adopt order (create records)\n        else Foreign order\n            RW->>EX: Cancel orphan order\n        end\n    end\n\n    alt Grid level has no active order (gap)\n        RW->>EX: Place new order at expected price/side\n        RW->>DB: Create Order + update GridLevel\n    end\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Risk Management\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant WS as WebSocket Listener\n    participant EX as Bybit Exchange\n    participant RM as Grid::RiskManager\n    participant DB as PostgreSQL\n    participant RD as Redis\n    participant AC as ActionCable\n    participant FE as Frontend\n\n    EX-->>WS: tickers: price update\n    WS->>RD: Update grid:{bot_id}:current_price\n    WS->>RM: RiskManager.check!(bot, current_price)\n\n    alt Price ≤ stop_loss_price OR ≥ take_profit_price\n        RM->>DB: Bot → stopping\n        RM->>EX: POST /v5/order/cancel-all\n        RM->>