tener** (`bin/ws_listener`) | Detects fills instantly | < 100ms |\n| **OrderFillWorker** (Sidekiq critical) | Places counter-orders, records trades | < 500ms |\n| **ReconciliationWorker** (Sidekiq default) | Catches missed fills, repairs gaps | 15s interval |\n| **BalanceSnapshotWorker** (Sidekiq cron) | Tracks portfolio value over time | 5min interval |\n| **DCP (Dead Man's Switch)** | Exchange cancels all orders if bot dies | 40s timeout |\n| **ActionCable** | Pushes real-time updates to frontend | Instant |\n| **Redis** | Hot cache for dashboard reads | Sub-ms |\n\n### The Profit Mechanism\n\n```\nPrice range: $2400 - $2600, 10 levels, step = $20\n\nLevel 10: $2600 SELL ←───┐\nLevel  9: $2580 SELL      │ Sell fills → place buy below\nLevel  8: $2560 SELL      │ profit = step × qty - fees\nLevel  7: $2540 (skip)    │\nLevel  6: $2520 (skip)    │ ← current price ~$2530\nLevel  5: $2500 BUY       │\nLevel  4: $2480 BUY       │ Buy fills → place sell above\nLevel  3: $2460 BUY  ─────┘\nLevel  2: $2440 BUY\nLevel  1: $2420 BUY\n```\n\nEach completed buy→sell cycle captures ~$20 × quantity minus fees. The bot profits from **volatility within the range**, regardless of price direction. Risk: price exits the range (handled by stop-loss/trailing).",
